I think this code is responsible for putting the last line as well as the cursor position:
```c
// from line 11279 in eval.c
TV_LIST_ITER_CONST(argvars[0].vval.v_list, li, {
    msg_puts(tv_get_string(TV_LIST_ITEM_TV(li)));
    msg_putchar('\n');
  });
```
Removing the newline would be complicated... Also, how do we change the cursor position? It stays at the position that `msg_putchar()` or `msg_puts()` leaves it.

